metadata.dc:description: The prognosis as to reproduction of patients with two surgical procedures for the tubes for managing ectopic pregnancy, is very bad. Two cases of live intrauterine pregnancy, after two tubal pregnancies surgically managed, are presented. Salpingectomy and salpingostomy were carried out in one patient, and salpingostomy and salpingectomy in the other one. In world literature there are only 23 reported cases, since 1947.
metadata.dc:title: Embarazo ortotópico posterior a dos ectópicos. Informe de dos casos y revisión de la literatura.
[An orthotopic pregnancy after 2 ectopic ones. A report of 2 cases and review of the literature].
